<br>
Having levelled to 65, gained entrance to Valor and Storms, without a guild (or a guild capable of handling pop encounters) its like you hit a roadblock square on. <br>
<br>
The alternate quests are not good enough in my opinion to be a viable alternative for the non-uber. You will still either need to gather 2-3 groups of friends for BoT, or find a group of people to camp with you for a week or more to get into HoH. If you have this sort of support, guess what you have a guild if not in name.<br>
<br>
I've been content to sit in valor and storms for the past couple of months, but its getting old fast. I have been able to break it up a bit with farming tradeskill items for friends when I can't get a group, but ffs ... <br>
<br>
Feels like I am being pushed to guild again, this time by the game itself. The time committment required by raiding guilds just isn't my style, and with 6 months left on my degree I'm not signing up to any huge time sinks.<br>
<br>
I promised myself that if it ever became unfun to play, I would quit. I mostly sit around in tells with friends these days or help out with little things people need done or farmed, but I miss the variety of options for a &quot;casual&quot; player at level 60.<br>
<br>
